CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 30, 1962, pg. 4, reads: "Offering Aid - An unidentified woman and her small daughter carry boxes of clothing and food to members of the Copland family who were left homeless when fire destroyed their home in Wickhaven, Pa. According to Mrs. Copland, friends of all races have 'opened their hearts up to us.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Woman and girl carrying bundles and boxes of donated clothing to fire victims in Copland family, in Wickhaven, Pennsylvania
